The current which generates the slow a.h.p. is sensitive to various neurotransmitters which thereby attenuate spike frequency adaptation. Most notably, a rise in intracellular cyclic AMP and presumably, therefore, an activation of cyclic AMPdependent protein kinase (Nestler, Walaas & Greengard, 1984) will block the slow

